aiRecommendations.overall:
**Top Performers**

Corbin Brown continues to be the highest-performing creator by a significant margin, driving 42% of total views and consistently producing viral TOFU content. His AI-focused angles ("AI Agents," "Replaced My Team") resonate strongly — his December 2024 video alone generated 520K views and 1,800 conversions.

Thomas Frank Explains delivers the strongest mid-funnel engagement, with notably high click-through rates on Notion integration content. His audience skews toward productivity enthusiasts who convert well.

**What's Working**

- AI + automation angles dominate: videos mentioning "AI" in the title average 2.3x more views than non-AI titles
- December and April are peak months — likely driven by "year in review" and "new year" planning content cycles
- TOFU content generates volume, but MOFU content (Notion, productivity stacks) drives better conversion rates per view

**What Needs Attention**

- Avi Singh's channel has shown declining engagement since mid-2025 — consider refreshing the content brief or adjusting investment
- June-August 2025 saw a significant dip across all creators — summer seasonality may require adjusted posting schedules
- BOFU content is underrepresented (only 12% of posts) — consider commissioning more comparison and migration-focused videos

**Recommendation**

Double down on Corbin Brown's AI agent content for TOFU, shift Thomas Frank toward more MOFU conversion-focused videos, and pilot a BOFU series with Nicole van der Hoeven focused on enterprise use cases and technical integrations.

monthly.2024-10: October 2024 marked a solid start with 188K views across 4 posts. **Corbin Brown's automation overview** led the pack at 85K views. The channel mix was well-balanced across funnel stages. Key opportunity: the "Zapier vs Make" comparison by Thomas Frank drove strong engagement — competitive comparison content clearly resonates with the audience.
monthly.2024-12: **Breakout month.** December 2024 was the first million-view month (1.14M total), driven almost entirely by Corbin Brown's AI agent video (520K views, 1,800 conversions). This single post accounted for 51% of the month's conversions. Thomas Frank's "Ultimate Tutorial" also performed well at 310K views. The AI narrative clearly hit at the right time — end-of-year planning + AI hype cycle convergence.
monthly.2025-02: February 2025 was the **highest-performing month to date** at 2.48M views. Corbin Brown's viral hit about replacing his team with AI agents drove 1.2M views alone. However, conversion rates were notably lower (0.02% vs December's 0.31%) — suggesting the content attracted a broader but less intent-driven audience. Consider adding stronger CTAs to viral TOFU content.
monthly.2025-04: April 2025 peaked at **4.49M views** — the all-time high. Corbin Brown (2.1M) and Thomas Frank (1.4M) both produced viral hits. The YouTube automation angle by Thomas Frank was particularly clever — teaching automation to an audience that already creates content. Conversion rates remained modest at 0.017%, reinforcing the need for better MOFU follow-up.
monthly.2025-05: May 2025 delivered strong click numbers (**17.3K clicks** — highest ever) despite lower views than April. Corbin Brown's business-building angle resonated differently, attracting a more commercially-minded audience. Avi Singh's Power Automate comparison was a smart competitive play. The click-to-view ratio of 1.0% was the best we've seen.
monthly.2026-01: January 2026 started strong with 1.94M views. The "2026 trends" angle worked well for Corbin Brown (980K views). Nicole van der Hoeven's DevOps content, while lower in raw views, attracted a highly technical audience — consider tracking demo requests separately for BOFU content like this.
